Chloe smiled constantly, and Tari couldn't help but grin. Inwardly she was singing, &quot;not on my own, not on my own,&quot; over and over. Everything about this girl was wonderful. Tari hoped she wasn't dreaming the whole thing.<br>
<br>
It was in the park that things went wrong. On the way back to Tari's rooftop, Chloe spotted a small group of teens throwing knives into trees out of boredom.<br>
Tari motioned for Chloe to move back into the shadows. But Tari's foot caught on a tree root, and she tumbled loudly backwards.<br>
One of the boys looked up and saw them.<br>
Tari swore, scrambling to her feet. They couldn't outrun all of the gang. She wildly looked to Chloe for help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ayscandie>ayscandie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(8/11/03 4:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rooftops</span><hr size=1> Chloe's swiftly turned around, her eyes wide and blazing with fear.  Her heart pounded with anxiety as the group headed towards them, knives drawn and ready to play.  She planted her feet firmly on the ground,  and out of sheer instinct grabbed Tari's hand for comfort.  The boys in the gang circled them.  Chloe's eyes darted from side to side.  <br>
<br>
     &quot;What would you two lovely ladies be doing alone in a place like this?&quot; smirked the boy who had spotted them.  Chloe was getting angry already, and the voice in the back of her head had already begun to mumble in it's own distinctive language.  She looked helplessly at Tari, hoping she would know what to say and do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blake@collisionworld>Blake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(8/13/03 7:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rooftops</span><hr size=1> &quot;Uhm . . . &quot; Tari gripped Chloe's hand tighter and said intelligently, &quot;Nothing.&quot;<br>
&quot;Nothing?&quot; the boy, seemingly the leader, raised an eyebrow. &quot;So you'd have time to . . . &quot; he smirked at his friends, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>socialise</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;<br>
Tari thought about their options. They could run, and get outrun. They could scream, but no one whould hear them who would care. They could try and talk their way out of things, but she doubted she'd manage that alone.<br>
There was always violence, but with the boy's knives that didn't look promising.<br>
&quot;Socialise?&quot; She rambled frantically, &quot;Uhm, actually we have quite a hectic, er, schedule as it is, so maybe we could take a raincheck on that social thing, kay?&quot;<br>
This was met with silence, then the leader sniggered. On cue, the rest of the boys laughed loudly.<br>
&quot;Raincheck? But <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>we're</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> free now, aren't we?&quot;<br>
Tari looked across at the other girl, whispering, &quot;How are you with your fists Chloe?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ayscandie>ayscandie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(8/27/03 4:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rooftops</span><hr size=1> &quot;Um.. fists?&quot; Chloe stuttered &quot;I dunno...&quot; Her voice trailed off.  The voice in her head was screaming now.  She knew that if she got in a fight with these boys it would definitely set her demon off.  She didn't want to risk that.  She didn't want to risk her new friend Tari seeing the that part of her, her deep dark secret.  She knew it would probably scare her away.  The boy stepped towards them.  Chloe's grip on Tari's hand loosened.  Her eyes rolled backwards into her head... She tried to muffle the sound of the words coming out of her mouth....  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blake@collisionworld>Blake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(9/2/03 4:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rooftops</span><hr size=1> Tari jumped as Chloe began to speak . . . but not speak. A strange sound was whispering from behind her clenched teeth, something like a voice but as yet without words.<br>
Tari knew she didn't want to listen long enough to understand what the voice was saying.<br>
Chloe was sweating, her eyes had rolled back to the whites.<br>
The boys were glancing at each other, wide eyed and nervous.<br>
&quot;Look what you've done!&quot; Tari yelled, her voice cracking.<br>
Chloe jerked, lunging toward the first boy as if against her will. He screamed, turning and running as his gang scattered from her. The inhuman mutters and wails coming from something inside Chloe were enough to make Tari's blood run cold.<br>
&quot;Chloe, what is it? What's happening to you?&quot;<br>
The other girl just sank to her knees, her head tilting backwards. As the boys fled with their fear and their hatred, the fit seemed to be passing.<br>
&quot;Chloe? Are you alright?&quot; but Tari received no answer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ayscandie>ayscandie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(9/22/03 4:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rooftops</span><hr size=1> Chloe collapsed on the ground.  She heard the boys running off, screaming with fear and looking back in disgust.  She was sure Tari was bound to think she was a lunatic.  She raised her head and looked at Tari.  Tears rolled down her cheeks.  &quot;I'm...I'm sorry&quot; she stuttered.  Her head seared in pain.  She covered her face with her hands, sobbing.  &quot;I'm sorry...I can't help it...I just...&quot; She lost her words.  She looked back at Tari, expecting the worst.<br>
